Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
mark_physical_power_domains(25.10)          mark_physical_power_domains(25.10)

Name
       mark_physical_power_domains  -  Marks  the  physical power domains that
       need fences in case the power domains share the same primary supply net
       and the available supply net setting (if specified)

Syntax
       mark_physical_power_domains

       [-help]

       {-domains <physical_domain_list> | -reset | -checkOnly}

       [-groupPhyLogicalDomains {{<phyPd lpd1 lpd2> ...} ...}]

       Marks the physical power domains that need fences in case the power do-
       mains share the same primary supply net and the  available  supply  net
       setting (if specified). The command also enables the logical domains to
       exist without any fence.

       Note:  mark_physical_power_domains  needs to be called again (after the
       initial use), whenever the tool reads in an power  intent  file.  Else,
       the file content is not recognized.

Parameters
       -help  Prints  out the command usage. For a detailed description of the
              command and all its parameters, use the man command:

              man mark_physical_power_domains

       -checkOnly
              Checks the fence sharing against Power/Ground (P/G) nets.

       -domains <physical_domain_list>
              Marks listed power domains as physical domains (a physical power
              domain must have a fence). Once a physical domain is marked, the
              power domain sharing the same P/G nets (not marked in this  com-
              mand)  are  recognized  as logical domain (or fenceless domain).
              Therefore, this domain can be implemented without a  fence.  The
              instances  within  logical domain are placed within the fence of
              its corresponding physical domain. This parameter also  executes
              the-checkOnly parameter, by default.

              Note:  Default  power domain is not required to be marked, it is
              marked by default. This command needs to be  called  after  each
              run of commit_power_intent. Otherwise the physical/logical power
              domain information will be lost in the database.

       -groupPhyLogicalDomains {{<phyPd lpd1 lpd2> ...} ...}
              Groups a list of physical and logical domains for the mark_phys-
              ical_power_domains command.

       -reset Resets   the   status   marking   settings  after  running  com-
              mit_power_intent.

Example
       The following command marks PDdefault as physical domain:

       mark_physical_power_domains -domains {PDdefault}

Related Information
              * commit_power_intent

              * Low Power Design chapter in the Innovus User Guide

